  "prompt": "What is the best iOS calendar app that allows you to cross off EVENTS as you go through the day?",
  "response": "There are several iOS calendar apps that include features allowing you to mark off events as you complete them. While the best option may vary depending on your specific needs, here are a few popular choices:\n\n1. **Fantastical**: This app combines a calendar and task manager, allowing you to check off events as you complete them. Its natural language processing allows for quick event creation, and it has an intuitive interface.\n\n2. **Things 3**: Although primarily a task manager, Things 3 can be used for scheduling events and offers a seamless way to check off tasks and events as you complete them. It has a clean and user-friendly design.\n\n3. **Todoist**: This app is primarily a task manager but has strong calendar integration features. You can easily mark tasks (which can include events) as complete, and it supports natural language input as well.\n\n4. **Apple Calendar with Reminders**: If you prefer using native apps, you can use Apple Calendar in conjunction with the Reminders app. You can set up events in Calendar and use Reminders to create tasks that you can check off.\n\n5. **Google Calendar**: While more focused on scheduling, you can use it in conjunction with Google Tasks to create a system where you can check off events/tasks.\n\n6. **Any.do**: This app offers a calendar view along with task management and lets you easily mark things as done.\n\nWhen selecting the best app for your needs, consider factors like user interface, ease of use, integration with other services, and whether you prefer a comprehensive task manager or a traditional calendar-focused app.",
